# Architecture Rules

## Message Bus Pattern
- All inter-agent communication goes through the message bus
- Never call agent methods directly from other agents — use `bus.request()`
- Messages are `Message(sender, recipient, type, payload)` dataclasses
- Use `bus.request()` for request/response, `bus.publish()` for fire-and-forget

## Agent Structure
- Agents inherit from a base class with `handle(message)` method
- Agents must not import or reference other agents directly
- Agent state lives in Memory, not in agent instance variables
- Agent tools are registered via `ToolRegistry`, not hardcoded

## Gateway Pattern
- Gateway receives `InboundMessage` from channels, routes to bus
- Gateway handles approval flows (HITL) via `approval_id` correlation
- Channels are adapters — they translate platform-specific formats to `InboundMessage`
- Never put business logic in channel adapters

## Cold Mode Gate
- Every destructive action must pass Cold Mode's 5-step checklist
- Cold Mode is a hard gate, not a suggestion
- If Cold Mode blocks an action, log the reason and return error to user
